  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Part Time Admissons Counsellor (Korean speaker)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Admissions Counsellor:</strong></p><p><u><strong>Job Objective</strong></u></p><p>Responsible for ensuring the school's enrollment goals are met through effective strategies and practices. Continuously strive to learn and adopt best practices to improve customer engagement and experience.</p><p><u><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></u></p><ul><li>Exceed the school's customer recruitment goals.</li><li>Provide quick and appropriate responses to inbound inquiries via the website, emails, telephone, and walk-ins.</li><li>Conduct timely and proactive follow-ups on all leads to convert them into Marketing Qualified Leads (MQLs) and Sales Qualified Leads (SQLs).</li><li>Be highly responsive and proactive in all customer-facing tasks.</li><li>Ensure all potential customers have a positive experience, regardless of enrollment outcome.</li><li>Manage parents, students, governing bodies, and internal and external stakeholders with professionalism.</li><li>Oversee all communications and lead management processes.</li><li>Convert and close MQLs and SQLs into customers through one-on-one counseling and other appropriate sales techniques.</li><li>Provide accurate information about the school’s vision, values, teaching methodologies, and philosophy.</li><li>Organize all aspects of open days for prospective parents.</li><li>Perform any other ad hoc responsibilities assigned by the reporting manager.</li></ul><p><u><strong>Requirements</strong></u></p><ul><li>Minimum of 3 years of relevant work experience in organizations with high processing requirements. Experience in an International School is preferred.</li><li>At least 3 years of relevant sales and/or marketing experience.</li><li>Preferably with experience in admissions within the education industry.</li><li>Experience in methodical tasks requiring accuracy.</li><li>Experience communicating with clients in Korean.</li><li>Strong organizational skills with the ability to manage multiple tasks and priorities.</li><li>Ability to work independently and as part of a team in a fast-paced environment</li></ul>",
